<subSubSection pageId="79" pageNumber="524" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="79" pageNumber="524">
Belongs to the “slim sprites”, a group of slight rainforest 
<taxonomicName authority="Agroup" authorityName="Agroup" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Pseudagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[853,995,664,691]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="524">Pseudagrion</emphasis>
<misspelling pageNumber="524" type="misspelled">Agroup</misspelling>
</taxonomicName>
species that perch in a hanging position and favour sandy streams (
<taxonomicName authority="Pinhey, 1973" authorityName="Pinhey" authorityYear="1973" box="[169,496,739,766]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Pseudagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyathiforme">
<emphasis box="[169,333,739,766]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="524">P.cyathiforme</emphasis>
Pinhey, 
<number box="[439,496,739,766]" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Carletti &amp; Terzani, 1997" authorityName="Carletti &amp; Terzani" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Pseudagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simplicilaminatum">
<emphasis box="[559,803,739,766]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="524">
P. 
<misspelling pageNumber="524" type="misspelled">simplicilaminatum</misspelling>
</emphasis>
<misspelling pageNumber="524" type="misspelled">Carletti</misspelling>
&amp; 
<misspelling pageNumber="524" type="misspelled">Terzani</misspelling>
, 
<number box="[159,217,776,803]" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" value="1997.0">1997</number>
</taxonomicName>
) or soft-bottomed ponds, seeps and headwaters (
<taxonomicName authority="Karsch, 1899" authorityName="Karsch" authorityYear="1899" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Pseudagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hemicolon">
<emphasis box="[796,940,776,803]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="524">P. hemicolon</emphasis>
Karsch, 
<number box="[159,215,814,840]" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" value="1899.0">1899</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fraser, 1955" authorityName="Fraser" authorityYear="1955" box="[274,577,814,840]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Pseudagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thenartum">
<emphasis box="[274,423,814,840]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="524">P. thenartum</emphasis>
Fraser, 
<number box="[516,577,814,840]" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" value="1955.0">1955</number>
</taxonomicName>
). The present taxon is probably the sister-species of the similar and sympatric 
<taxonomicName box="[632,782,851,878]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Pseudagrion" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="79" pageNumber="524" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thenartum">
<emphasis box="[632,782,851,878]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="524">P. thenartum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but separated by the male appendages.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
